# PBX Stratos — example environment file
#
# Copy this to `.env` at the repo root and fill in your values. The
# actual `.env` is gitignored and ACL-locked to owner-only after the
# install scripts write to it.
#
# **NEVER commit, screenshot, or paste your real `.env` contents
# anywhere.** All secrets in this file should be treated as
# confidential.
#
# This example documents EVERY env var the framework reads. Most have
# sensible defaults and you don't need to set them. The only one you
# really need to think about is HELIUS_MAINNET_URL (for live trading).

# ============================================================
# Live trading master gate (the only one you usually set yourself)
# ============================================================
#
# The single env var that arms live trading. Without this set, every
# live endpoint returns 503 and no keypair is ever used to sign a
# transaction. This is by design — absence of the var IS the safety net.
#
# Get a free key at https://dashboard.helius.dev/api-keys (the free
# tier is plenty for personal use).
HELIUS_MAINNET_URL=

# ============================================================
# Bot secrets — auto-generated; you almost never set these by hand
# ============================================================
#
# These three live in `runtime/bots/local.env` (mode 0600), NOT here.
# The server generates them on first boot when STRATOS_ALLOW_AUTOGEN=1.
# Listed here purely for documentation — set them in `local.env` if
# you're importing wallets from somewhere else.

# 64 hex chars (32 random bytes). Token the dashboard uses to
# authenticate against the local bot API.
# BOT_API_TOKEN=

# 64 hex chars (32 random bytes). AES-256-GCM master key for
# at-rest wallet keypair encryption. LOSING THIS = LOSING ALL WALLETS.
# BOT_MASTER_KEY=

# 24-word BIP39 seed phrase. Every bot wallet you spawn derives from
# this phrase. LOSE THIS AND ALL DERIVED WALLETS ARE PERMANENTLY GONE.
# Back this up on PAPER, in a safe. Never in cloud storage unencrypted.
# BOT_HD_MNEMONIC=

# ============================================================
# Path overrides — auto-set by pm2.config.cjs; only override for testing
# ============================================================

# Repo root. Defaults to the directory containing `pm2.config.cjs`.
# STRATOS_REPO_ROOT=

# Directory where the server writes bot state, wallets, logs.
# Defaults to <repo>/runtime/bots. Server auto-creates if missing,
# refuses to operate on a symlink.
# STRATOS_BOTS_DATA_DIR=

# Directory for bot config files. Defaults to <repo>/runtime/config.
# STRATOS_BOTS_HOME=

# Directory the decoder + paper trader write to. Defaults to
# <repo>/runtime/lab.
# STRATOS_LAB_HOME=

# Set to "1" to allow the server to autogenerate BOT_API_TOKEN +
# BOT_MASTER_KEY + BOT_HD_MNEMONIC into <STRATOS_BOTS_DATA_DIR>/local.env
# on first boot. The install scripts set this; production deploys
# should NOT — they should pre-provision the secrets explicitly.
# STRATOS_ALLOW_AUTOGEN=

# Override the default URL for the cold-start air-quality dataset
# backfill. Defaults to https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Typ0x/pbx-air-quality-dataset/main
# Set this if you're mirroring the dataset elsewhere.
# STRATOS_AIRQ_DATASET_URL=

# ============================================================
# Server runtime — defaults are fine; override for dev
# ============================================================

# Dashboard port. Defaults to 8787.
# PORT=8787

# Bind host. Defaults to 127.0.0.1 (localhost only). Setting to
# 0.0.0.0 exposes the dashboard to your LAN — only do this if you
# understand the security implications.
# HOST=127.0.0.1

# pino log verbosity. One of: trace, debug, info, warn, error, fatal.
# LOG_LEVEL=info
